      "description": "Offering an exceptional 997.1 Carrera S, maintained to concours standards. The 3.8L flat-six delivers linear power with zero bore scoring issues, paired with a precise 6-speed manual transaxle and a factory short-shift kit. Mechanically flawless, the chassis retains its original rigidity, supported by a recalibrated PASM system and crisp turn-in via refreshed bushings. The M97/01 power unit exhibits perfect compression across all cylinders, and the cooling system has been proactively overhauled. This is a turn-key example for the discerning purist seeking a visceral, naturally aspirated experience in its most pristine form.",
